_:N393309a6858a4b359997d540fae07106 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>John Healey was appointed Secretary of State for Defence on 5 July 2024. He was elected as the MP for Rawmarsh and Conisbrough in July 2024.</p>\n\n<p>He was Shadow Housing Secretary from 2015 to 2020 and Shadow Health Secretary from 2010-2011. During Labour’s time in Government, John was PPS to the Chancellor of the Exchequer from 1999-2001 and a Minister from 2001-2010, serving successively as Adult Skills Minister, Treasury Minister, Local Government Minister and Housing Minister.</p>\n\n<p>Before entering Parliament, John was Campaigns Director at the Trades Union Congress and a disability rights campaigner.</p>\n\n<p>John is married with one son and lives in Rotherham.</p>\n" .
